From 49b1af5cdbc5fc8cd384010e73b614a7713e3f25 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jason Pepas <jasonpepas@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 00:46:19 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] os.c: gate <spawn.h> include behind JANET_NO_POSIX_SPAWN

Tiger / pre-Leopard macOS lacks <spawn.h> and macports-legacy-support
does not backfill posix_spawn{,p}.  Introduce a positive feature
flag JANET_NO_POSIX_SPAWN that, when defined, both skips the
<spawn.h> include and selects an alternate fork+execve code path
inside os_execute_impl (next commit).

This is the include-side half of the change; the implementation-
side fallback follows.
---
 src/core/os.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/core/os.c b/src/core/os.c
index bc7b7bd6..7aed38d8 100644
--- a/src/core/os.c
+++ b/src/core/os.c
@@ -58,7 +58,7 @@
 #include <process.h>
 #define JANET_SPAWN_CHDIR
 #else
-#ifndef JANET_PLAN9
+#if !defined(JANET_PLAN9) && !defined(JANET_NO_POSIX_SPAWN)
 #include <spawn.h>
 #endif
 #include <utime.h>
